<%= render "layouts/header" %>
<div class="font-tempbugfix">
    <div class="overflow-x-hidden">
        <div class="relative">
            <div class="mt-8 mx-auto max-w-screen-xl px-4 sm:mt-12 sm:px-6 md:mt-20 xl:mt-24">
                <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-12 lg:gap-8">
                    <div class="sm:text-center md:max-w-2xl md:mx-auto lg:col-span-6 lg:text-left">
                        <h2 class="mt-1 text-4xl tracking-tight leading-10 font-extrabold text-indigo-600 sm:leading-none sm:text-6xl lg:text-5xl xl:text-6xl">
                            Improve
                            <br class="hidden md:inline" />
                            <span class="text-gray-900">Your Workflow</span>
                            <span class="text-indigo-600">With Agilely</span>
                        </h2>
                        <p class="mt-3 text-base text-gray-500 sm:mt-5 sm:text-xl lg:text-lg xl:text-xl">
                            Agilely is a simple and intuitive project management solution based on the kanban prinicples.
                        </p>
                        <div class="mt-5 sm:mt-8 sm:flex sm:justify-center lg:justify-start">
                            <div class="rounded-md shadow">
                                <%= link_to new_user_registration_path do %>
                                <button class="w-full flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-3 border border-transparent text-base leading-6 font-medium rounded-md text-white bg-indigo-600 hover:bg-indigo-500 focus:outline-none focus:shadow-outline transition duration-150 ease-in-out md:py-4 md:text-lg md:px-10">
                                    Get Started &rarr;
                                </button>
                                <% end %>
                            </div>
                            <div class="mt-3 sm:mt-0 sm:ml-3">
                                <%= link_to pricing_path do %>
                                <button class="w-full flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-3 border border-transparent text-base leading-6 font-medium rounded-md text-indigo-600 bg-indigo-100 hover:text-indigo-500 hover:bg-white focus:outline-none focus:shadow-outline focus:border-indigo-300 transition duration-150 ease-in-out md:py-4 md:text-lg md:px-10">
                                    View Pricing
                                </button>
                                <% end %>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mt-12 relative sm:max-w-lg sm:mx-auto lg:mt-0 lg:max-w-none lg:mx-0 lg:col-span-6 lg:flex lg:items-center">
                        <div class="relative mx-auto w-full lg:max-w-md">
                            <%= image_pack_tag 'tasks.svg'%>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="px-6 bg-body mt-24">
        <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
            <div class="text-center py-6 px-6">
                <div class="text-4xl text-indigo-600 font-bold">The three principles of Kanban</div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-row-reverse items-center md:flex md:-mx-6">
                <div class="md:w-1/2 md:px-6">
                    <%= image_pack_tag 'kanbanboard.svg', class: "max-w-full rounded shadow-lg", alt: "a kanban board" %>
                </div>
                <div class="mt-10 md:w-1/2 md:px-6 md:mt-0">
                    <h3 class="mb-0 text-3xl font-extrabold leading-tight">
                        <span class="block mb-2 text-lg font-bold text-indigo-600">
                            Visualization
                        </span>
                        Visualize your workflow
                    </h3>
                    <p class="mt-2 mb-0 text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 sm:text-xl">
                        In Kanban, everything starts with a kanban board. Every
                        board, has columns, often labeled 'to-do', 'doing', and
                        'done'. Columns are filled with cards, which are work items.
                        As work gets completed, your cards flow from left to right.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="py-20">
            <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
                <div class="items-center md:flex md:-mx-6">
                    <div class="md:w-1/2 md:px-6">
                        <%= image_pack_tag 'focus.svg', class: "max-w-full rounded shadow-lg", alt: "start working!" %>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mt-10 md:w-1/2 md:px-6 md:mt-0">
                        <h3 class="mb-0 text-3xl font-extrabold leading-tight">
                            <span class="block mb-2 text-lg font-bold text-indigo-600">
                                Work
                            </span>
                            Start with what you do now
                        </h3>
                        <p class="mt-2 mb-0 text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 sm:text-xl">
                            Kanban does not tell you how to work, it's just an
                            organization tool. Start with your highest priorities in the
                            'to-do' column, and work from there.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="py-20">
            <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
                <div class="flex-row-reverse items-center md:flex md:-mx-6">
                    <div class="md:w-1/2 md:px-6">
                        <%= image_pack_tag 'improve.svg', class: "max-w-full rounded shadow-lg", alt: "always improving" %>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mt-10 md:w-1/2 md:px-6 md:mt-0">
                        <h3 class="mb-0 text-3xl font-extrabold leading-tight">
                            <span class="block mb-2 text-lg font-bold text-indigo-600">
                                Improvement
                            </span>
                            Constantly improve and evolve
                        </h3>
                        <p class="mt-2 mb-0 text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 sm:text-xl">
                            As you get used to the workflow, you should be constantly
                            improving and reacting to changes in your environment.
                            Improvement is a key aspect in any project.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full relative bg-indigo-500 py-16 mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-white text-4xl font-bold text-center">
            Get Started Today!
        </h3>
        <h5 class="text-indigo-200 text-xl text-center mb-8">
            Free for personal use, no credit card required.
        </h5>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="bg-gray-800">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="-mt-24 bg-white relative rounded-lg mt-4 max-w-2xl mx-auto py-10 px-6">
            <div class="max-w-lg mx-auto sm:flex sm:overflow-hidden px-2">
                <%= link_to new_user_registration_path do %>
                <button class="border border-indigo-600 rounded text-white sm:flex-1 text-lg px-6 py-3 md:px-8 md:py-5 bg-indigo-600 rounded-lg sm:rounded-r-none w-full sm:w-auto block sm:border-r-0 focus:outline-none hover:bg-indigo-500">
                    Create a free account</button>
                <% end %>
                <%= link_to pricing_path do %>
                <button class="mt-2 sm:mt-0 border border-gray-400 rounded text-gray-700 sm:flex-1 text-lg px-6 py-3 md:px-8 md:py-5 bg-white rounded-lg sm:rounded-l-none w-full sm:w-auto block border-2 border-gray-300 sm:border-l-0 bg-gray-100 focus:bg-white focus:border-gray-400 focus:outline-none hover:bg-gray-200 hover:text-gray-600">
                    View our team pricing
                </button>
                <% end %>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="text-gray-500 text-center py-12">
        Â© 2020 | Agilely.com
    </div>
</div>